Class Saros

  • java.lang.Object
    • jparsec.ephem.event.Saros

  • public class Saros
extends java.lang.Object
    Obtain Saros data for certain eclipse.

    This class provides methods for obtaining a list of eclipses and their Saros data. Here is a possible output data from results taken exclusively from this class.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Saros

        public Saros(double jd)
      throws JPARSECException
        Obtain saros information for an eclipse that occurs around certain Julian day. Eclipse date and type are obtained from approximate assumptions, and it is not recommended for far away epochs.
        Parameters:
        jd - Julian day of eclipse.
        Throws:
        JPARSECException - If an error occurs.

      • Saros

        public Saros(double jd,
     SimpleEventElement.EVENT type)
      throws JPARSECException
        Obtain saros information for an eclipse that occurs around certain Julian day. Results are set to static variables. Eclipse date and type are supposed to be input date and type.
        Parameters:
        jd - Julian day of eclipse.
        type - The eclipse type.
        Throws:
        JPARSECException - If an error occurs.

    • Method Detail

      • getAllEclipses

        public static java.util.ArrayList<double[]> getAllEclipses(double jd_initial,
                                           double jd_final)
                                                    throws JPARSECException
        Deprecated. The methods in MainEvents should be used instead.
        Find all eclipses between two dates, including all saros information. Algorithm is approximate, and only valid in current epoch.
        Parameters:
        jd_initial - Initial jd to search in TT.
        jd_final - Final jd to search in TT.
        Returns:
        A set of double precission arrays, with the following information ordered:

        - Julian day of the eclipse in TT (maximum, with an accuracy up to one or two minutes).

        - Eclipse type, solar or lunar. The value is the ordinal of the eclipse type enumeration defined in this class.

        - Eclipse subtype, ID constants defined in SolarEclipse class (even for lunar eclipses). For penumbral lunar eclipses, the constant type_no_eclipse is used.

        - Saros series.

        - Inex number.

        - Eclipse number in the current saros series.

        - Number of the last eclipse in the current saros series.

        Throws:
        JPARSECException - If an error occurs.
